import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    data_merged = world.set_index('name').join(data.set_index('country'))
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 10))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    
    data_merged.plot(column='pop', ax=ax, legend=True, cax=cax, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of population across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    life_expect_by_year = data.groupby('year')['life_expect'].mean()

    plt.plot(life_expect_by_year.index, life_expect_by_year.values, label='Life Expectancy')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('How has life expectancy changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], c=data['cluster'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.8)
    ax.set_xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Clusters")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    cluster_counts = data.groupby(['country', 'cluster']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    ax = cluster_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(15, 6))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of clusters across different countries?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Country")
    plt.ylabel("Cluster Count")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(title="Cluster", loc="upper left")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
